WEBVTT

00:00.540 --> 00:01.950
Previously on <i>Medium...</i>

00:01.960 --> 00:05.880
<i>"Gunshots have repeatedly been fired inside 
the offices of AERODYTECH"</i>

00:05.930 --> 00:07.410
Has anyone seen Joe Dubois?

00:10.490 --> 00:11.810
-So you ready for this?

00:11.820 --> 00:13.180
-As ready as i'd ever be.

00:13.230 --> 00:14.740
-Welcome back, Joe
-Thank you

00:15.170 --> 00:19.400
Is everything okay at work?
Is everything okay with us?

00:19.410 --> 00:20.450
Everything is fine.

00:20.500 --> 00:21.590
Something seems wrong.

00:21.630 --> 00:22.590
<i>Mrs. Dubois,</i>

00:22.630 --> 00:24.590
My name is Marcus Canty.

00:24.630 --> 00:25.790
I work with your husband.

00:25.830 --> 00:27.150
Since he's come back to work,

00:27.200 --> 00:28.920
<i>he hasn't been attending any meetings,</i>

00:28.960 --> 00:30.950
<i>he hasn't been making any phone calls.</i>

00:31.000 --> 00:32.420
<i>Your boss called.</i>

00:32.460 --> 00:34.890
They said they might
want you to see someone.

00:34.930 --> 00:36.320
My name is Cooper Conroy.

00:36.360 --> 00:37.490
I'm an attorney,Mr. Dubois.

00:37.530 --> 00:38.720
Can you talk for a moment?

00:38.760 --> 00:40.190
Talk about what?

00:40.230 --> 00:43.620
About millions of dollars I
believe you're entitled to.

00:43.890 --> 00:46.820
<i>I dream the same dream every night,</i>

00:46.860 --> 00:48.990
and there is nothing
circumstantial about it.

00:49.030 --> 00:50.650
We're going to finish trying this case.

00:50.700 --> 00:51.990
We're going to trust the jury.

00:52.030 --> 00:53.320
We find the defendant

00:53.360 --> 00:56.650
guilty of murder in first degree.

00:56.700 --> 00:58.590
Thank you for the encouragement.

00:58.630 --> 01:00.320
I work for the District Attorney,

01:00.360 --> 01:01.650
Manuel Devalos.

01:01.700 --> 01:02.820
It's not that exciting.

01:02.860 --> 01:04.090
Easy for you to say.

01:04.129 --> 01:05.319
You don't sell
pharmaceuticals for a living.

01:05.360 --> 01:06.350
So...

01:06.400 --> 01:08.350
what's it like working for the DA?

01:08.400 --> 01:11.220
I thought you needed
to see this. Oh,my God.

01:11.260 --> 01:15.190
It's Natalie Paxton's head
on Ramona Hensley's body.

01:15.230 --> 01:16.720
<i>City Hall is already being inundated</i>

01:16.760 --> 01:17.950
with people calling for
the immediate release

01:18.000 --> 01:19.690
of Walter Paxton.

01:21.130 --> 01:22.520
You expecting a calltoday... It's okay.

01:22.560 --> 01:24.790
...or maybe a text?

01:24.830 --> 01:27.190
<i>My husband's kind of
going through something.</i>

01:27.230 --> 01:28.690
Well,now we know where the head

01:28.730 --> 01:30.220
of the third victim ended up.

01:30.260 --> 01:31.620
So who's the body belong to?

01:31.660 --> 01:34.190
Driver's license photo.

01:36.000 --> 01:42.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:45.210 --> 01:46.770
Hey,Dad.

01:47.140 --> 01:48.320
Evening,son.

01:48.330 --> 01:49.380
<i>So...</i>

01:49.400 --> 01:50.890
what's all the hubbub?

01:50.930 --> 01:52.390
Huh?

01:52.430 --> 01:56.120
What's so important you needed
to raise me from the dead?

01:56.170 --> 01:59.560
Well,I was just kind
of reviewing my options,

01:59.600 --> 02:02.590
contemplating my future.

02:02.630 --> 02:04.220
Well,you know,I don't get you.

02:04.270 --> 02:05.490
I don't know what you're talking about.

02:05.530 --> 02:06.790
What's to contemplate?

02:06.830 --> 02:09.320
I mean,your future's right here.

02:09.370 --> 02:11.090
You got the,the two kids...

02:11.130 --> 02:12.790
Three.

02:12.830 --> 02:16.390
...the happy marriage
to Haley Joel Osment.

02:16.430 --> 02:19.390
Yeah,I know,I know.

02:19.430 --> 02:20.790
I just...

02:20.830 --> 02:24.290
There were five of us in that room,Dad.

02:24.330 --> 02:27.390
Only two of us made it out alive.

02:27.430 --> 02:28.820
Why me?

02:28.870 --> 02:30.020
Why not them?

02:32.070 --> 02:35.920
Because.

02:35.970 --> 02:37.620
That's it?

02:37.670 --> 02:39.160
That's your answer?

02:39.200 --> 02:41.420
"Because"?

02:41.470 --> 02:43.220
You know what your problem is?

02:43.270 --> 02:45.290
You've never been in a war.

02:45.330 --> 02:48.790
My generation... we saw death,

02:48.830 --> 02:51.320
contemplated our own
mortality when we were young

02:51.370 --> 02:52.590
so we didn't have to waste

02:52.630 --> 02:55.020
the rest of our lives worrying about it.

02:55.070 --> 02:57.590
We realized that death
takes care of itself.

02:57.630 --> 03:01.060
It's life that needs your attention.

03:01.100 --> 03:03.520
Life,huh?

03:04.930 --> 03:07.660
Look,you got a great job.
You got a hot little wife.

03:07.700 --> 03:09.990
You got a couple of nice kids,

03:10.030 --> 03:13.690
and here you are
wondering why you're alive.

03:13.730 --> 03:15.120
You know what you need to do?

03:15.170 --> 03:16.290
What's that?

03:16.330 --> 03:18.290
You need to wake up. Oh,really?

03:18.330 --> 03:19.620
I mean it.

03:19.670 --> 03:21.060
Honey,I need you to wake up.

03:21.100 --> 03:22.290
Honey? Darling.

03:22.330 --> 03:24.260
Please,just wake up.

03:24.300 --> 03:25.860
Wait a second. No,I'm confused.

03:25.900 --> 03:26.860
Why should I?

03:28.000 --> 03:30.990
Give me one good reason.

03:31.030 --> 03:34.690
Because I need to talk to
you about a dream I just had.

03:34.730 --> 03:36.920
<i>So they found your friend's body</i>

03:36.970 --> 03:39.590
with the head of the third victim on it?

03:39.630 --> 03:42.220
That would make your
friend the fourth victim.

03:42.270 --> 03:43.420
Uh-huh.

03:44.900 --> 03:47.760
To be honest,I don't think the
issue is as much who to call

03:47.800 --> 03:49.320
as it is what to say.

03:49.370 --> 03:50.560
Well,I have to tell someone.

03:50.600 --> 03:51.920
What are you going to tell them?

03:51.970 --> 03:53.360
"I don't know who the next victim is,

03:53.400 --> 03:55.460
but I can tell you about
the one after that"?

03:55.500 --> 03:57.620
<i>It's not as if you know when
any of this is going to happen.</i>

03:57.670 --> 03:59.260
Are you saying I shouldn't tell anybody?

03:59.300 --> 04:00.660
I don't know.

04:00.700 --> 04:03.790
Keep in mind this is a dream
you had after two martinis.

04:03.830 --> 04:06.390
Uh... I'm not telling you

04:06.430 --> 04:07.520
how to do your job.

04:07.570 --> 04:08.590
I'm just saying that I don't think

04:08.630 --> 04:10.190
there's anyone to call tonight.

04:10.230 --> 04:13.920
Right.

04:13.970 --> 04:16.959
Speaking of calling,how's your phone?

04:17.000 --> 04:19.959
Very clean.

04:20.000 --> 04:22.160
Useless,but very clean.

04:23.230 --> 04:25.390
Melinda had her baby...

04:25.430 --> 04:28.320
and that's who keeps texting me.

04:28.370 --> 04:31.290
She asked about you,by the way.

04:31.330 --> 04:32.860
How you're doing.

04:32.900 --> 04:35.420
How you're doing with me.

04:35.470 --> 04:38.820
Tell her not very well.

04:42.630 --> 04:44.590
But I'm determined to change that.

04:44.630 --> 04:47.760
Yeah.

04:47.800 --> 04:49.890
Me,too.

